				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${T_{n + 1}} = a{P_n}.$$\end{document} Now, because flux eruption is a fast process, the strength of the poloidal field at cycle n + 1 is (nonlinearly) proportional to the toroidal field strength of the current cycle: 39\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
